[05:41.13]We perceived a low carriage, fixed on a sledge and drawn by dogs, pass on towards the north, at the distance of half a mile;  a being which had the shape of a man, but apparently of gigantic stature, sat in the sledge and guided the dogs.   We watched the rapid progress of the traveller with our telescopes until he was lost among the distant inequalities of the ice. 
